Russian President Vladimir Putin has signed a law on the introduction of administrative liability for violation of the deadline and order of payment of goods (work, services) when making purchases for state and municipal needs.
This law is intended to solve the very sharp problem of non-fulfillment of its obligations by customers in the implementation of state and municipal procurement.
Another two years ago, the situation when entrepreneurs could not get payment for the already executed state and municipal contracts, was universal.
At the same time, the President of Russia gave the order to the General Prosecutor's Office of the Russian Federation to take the problem on special control.
Because the businessmen themselves could not deal with unfair customers who signed unfinanced contracts, attempted to escape from paid obligations and included illegal conditions in the contracts.
The problem was systematic in the country.
Since 2015, in the interests of the protection of the rights of entrepreneurs to receive payments on public orders by the prosecutor's office, 9,7 thousand submissions have been submitted, according to the results of their consideration to disciplinary responsibility, 4,5 thousand officials have been attracted, to the administrative - 533, to the investigative bodies for the organization of processal checks, 75 materials have been submitted, 46 of which have been incurred criminal cases.
In the end, the debt to entrepreneurs in the amount of more than 66 billion rubles was paid.
And these huge amounts accumulated far from the result of the non-payment of billions of contracts.
Numerous, systematic delays in paying services to entrepreneurs have led to basic debts to much more modest amounts.
This is a characteristic case.
The head of a small company won a competition for social transport services for several million rubles.
The man invested all his turnover funds, fully fulfilled his obligations, but the money placed in time did not receive.
The result is an increasing financial cum of debts on wages, taxes, loans, which would lead to bankruptcy if the entrepreneur did not seek help to the prosecutor's office.
Now, in a number of regions, the problem has been reduced as much as possible.
However, in the first half of 2017, the total amount of debt on state and municipal contracts, identified by the prosecutors of subjects of the Russian Federation, amounted to about 27.4 billion rubles.
In regions where debt rates continue to reach critical values, the prosecutor's office works in a manual anti-crisis management mode.
The Prosecutor General personally holds exit meetings with the representatives of the local authorities, on which all the offences opened by the Prosecutors and measures for their immediate elimination are subjectly discussed.
Such operational meetings have already been held this year in Yaroslavl and Yekaterinburg.
The Federal Law No. 189-FZ "On Amendments to the Code of the Russian Federation on Administrative Crimes in Part of the Establishment of Administrative Liability of Officials of the Customer for Violation of the Term and Order of Payment of Goods (Works, Services) During Purchasing for State and Municipal Needs" was signed last week by the President of the Russian Federation.
The draft law was developed by the Ministry of Economic Development of Russia on the initiative of the General Prosecutor's Office.
The new law will supplement the Code of the Russian Federation on administrative offences by an article, which provides a fine from 30 thousand to 50 thousand rubles for violation by the official of the customer of the period and order of payment of goods, works and services in state and municipal purchases.
And if the official has already been sentenced to administrative punishment for a similar offence, he is disqualified for a period of one year to two years.
All the prosecutors of the subjects of the Russian Federation have already received an order to ensure the application of these legislative novels in practice.
