The order and place of the swear will be determined by the President.
Where and how new Russian citizens will swear to the loyalty of the Russian Federation, will be determined by the President - such amendments to the second reading of the relevant law developed by the State Duma Committee on Legislation and State Building.
A week ago, the parliamentarians planned to directly determine the procedure for making the oath in the law.
Children under the age of 18 will be released from the ceremonial oath, as well as those who are unable, according to the updated text of the amendments to the draft law "On citizenship of the Russian Federation" (it is at the disposal of "Izvestij"), which the committee on July 11 will consider before the second reading at its meeting.
The idea of introducing a sword when entering the Russian citizenship instead of the formal signature of the documents President Vladimir Putin supported on June 6 during a meeting with the Speaker of the State Duma Vyacheslav Vladimir.
Deputies formed this idea in the form of an amendment to the second reading to a bill that provides for the cancellation of the decision on granting citizenship to those who were subsequently convicted of a number of crimes of terrorist or extremist nature: for example, for public calls to terrorism or its public justification in the media or on the internet (Article 2 article 205.2 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation), as well as for the kidnapping of a plane, train or water transport, but only if this act is related to terrorism (Article 4 article 211 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation).
According to the draft law, its logic was the following: by formulating the documents for citizenship, a person signs under a promise to comply with the Russian legislation - a rule on the way of extremism, he breaks this promise.
The bill was submitted to the State Duma in April by the leaders of the Duma factions Vladimir Vasilyev ("United Russia"), Gennady Zyuganov (KPRF), Vladimir Zhirinovsky (LDPR), Sergey Mironov ("Justice Russia") and the spokesman of the Duma Vyacheslav Volodin.
The members of the Parliament accepted it in the first reading on 19 May.
Last week, the DG Committee on State Building and Legislation approved the text of the bill for second reading, but now it has been revised again.
Now it says that the order of swearing will be established by the President of the Russian Federation.
Previously, the parliamentarians intended to describe the procedure directly in the law "On the citizenship of the Russian Federation", indicating that the ceremony should be held in a ceremonial setting in front of the state herb and flag of Russia in the presence of a representative of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs.
However, it was not clear from the text of the bill where such an event should be held - a list of places where the herb of the Russian Federation can be placed, regulated by the relevant federal constitutional law.
These include courts, cabinets of heads of state bodies of subjects, municipal institutions, judges, prosecutors, heads of federal executive bodies, etc.
Most likely, it could also be ZAGS.
Those who wish to obtain Russian citizenship will make a solemn swear after officials check their documents.
But the Russian passport will only be obtained by a person after he has brought a swear, according to the pre-worked text.
A week ago the draft stated that the oath should be preceded by the signature of the decree.
In the updated text, it is said that Russia will swear from 18 years, not from 14.
The rule is retained by which the unable or limited-capable will be exempt from the sworn, as well as those who cannot speak, read or sign the text of the sworn.
In addition, the President of the Russian Federation has the right to exempt from this procedure and “other persons”,
Also, the updated bill provides a special order of reception to Russian citizens of the residents of Ukraine, who are considered to be Russian language carriers.
They will have to officially refuse the Ukrainian citizenship by submitting an appropriate declaration to the authorized body of Ukraine.
Notarily certified copy of the statement will be submitted to Russian officials.
The withdrawal of “foreign” citizenship, as it is now, will not be required if it is provided by an international treaty or if it is impossible “for reasons that do not depend on the person”.
The corresponding amendment to the law was proposed by a group of deputies, among which the first vice-speaker of the DG Ivan Melnikov (KPRF), Natalia Poklonskaya, Pavel Krasheninnikov and Ayrat Farahov (all - "United Russia").
I think many of you know that getting a certificate from Ukraine is unrealistic, simply impossible.
Accordingly, very many people are waiting for a decision of their fate on the citizenship of the Russian Federation, - explained the head of the Duma Committee on State Building and Legislation Pavel Krasheninnikov (ER).
In addition, the text has been clarified that the restrictions on occupation of certain positions for foreigners will not apply to those who have writtenly refused the "other" citizenship and delivered the previous passport to the Russian Ministry of Foreign Affairs, but "for non-dependent reasons" he has not ceased to be considered a citizen of another country.
Currently, foreigners are forbidden to occupy positions in the municipal service, to be accepted to work on facilities and in organizations whose activities are related to the security of Russia.
Also, a person with a double citizenship or a visa for residence in another country cannot become a member of the State Duma or a member of the Council of the Federation.
It is planned that the law should enter into force from 1 September 2017, at that time the necessary sub-legislative acts must be prepared.
