Islamists are in the coalition.
Yes, but he himself adheres to the position that Libya should be an absolutely normal country – moderate Islamic, open to the world.
He is also actively fighting terrorists.
Where does this reputation come from?
It is created by those countries that are not interested in Russia to communicate with Tripoli.
Tripoli is the capital, there is legislative, executive and judicial power.
There is a national oil corporation, a national bank and other government structures.
Of course, some countries were interested in not getting there.
And we mixed all the maps and began to communicate actively with Tripoli and Tobruk.
And we’re already eating the fruit of this work: Rosneft has signed an agreement on cooperation with the state oil company of Libya – NOC.
NOC Director Mustafa Sanalla, with whom the head of Rosnefty Igor Sechin had a deal, himself directly from Tripoli.
Two weeks ago, the first shipment of Libyan oil was made by Rosneft.
What will Russia do with it?
I think to sell again.
What are the economic interests of Russia in Libya?
The plans are to re-sign contracts concluded with Muammar al-Qaeda.
It is about previous agreements in the transport sector (Railway construction), energy (electricity) and a number of others.
Does the Libyan have something to pay?
They have oil.
That is, as in the case with Iran, it is a “oil in exchange for services” scheme?
I don’t know what the scheme will be, I don’t deal with these issues directly.
In fact, the economy for Russia in Libya is not the most important.
We are actually working on peace.
For us, the main thing is to stop the bloodshed, to help the Libyan people agree with each other so that they can establish order and Libya has ceased to be a favorable environment for the development of terrorism.
For Russia, this is the main task of helping the Libyan people and expelling terrorists from there.
Do you have data about the presence in Libya (now or earlier) of radical militants from Russia or other countries of the former USSR?
One of the tasks of our contact group was to find out this.
I met with a representative of the Libyan State Security Committee, who said that at the moment there is no exit from Russia and other countries of the former USSR there.
He said he had about 50 thousand records of telephone conversations of representatives of Islamist and radical groups (in Libya. - "Ъ") and the Russian speech there doesn't sound.
And from which countries are these militants?
I’t want to go into these details.
Then we formulate the question differently.
How many of the Islamist militants in Libya are Libyans themselves?
There are almost no Libyan among them, they are not more than 5%.
The rest are coming.
Can Moscow conduct intra-Libyan talks on the example of Paris?
There are such plans.
We are conducting active talks with the Libyan people, several delegations from Libya have already visited Moscow, and have declared their willingness to come again - to Moscow or to Grozny.
When can such negotiations take place?
It is hard to say now.
There are still a few visits to be held, and then I hope there will be clarity about the time and place of negotiations.
