In Russia, two new territories of advanced socio-economic development will appear - "Abaza" and "Novotroitsk".
The relevant rulings of the Government of the Russian Federation will enter into force today, August 4.
The boundaries and types of economic activity of the TOR are defined in the territory of the city of Abaza in the Republic of Hakasia.
In the city, where there are 15,000 people, a special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity, as well as the minimum amount of capital investments of residents, the minimum number of new permanent jobs will be in effect.
It is expected that this will attract about 2.5 billion rubles of investment in the city, and will also create more than 600 new jobs.
The list of types of economic activities in which the TOR "Abaza" will operate a special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity, for example, plants, livestock, food production, non-alcoholic beverages and clothing.
The Government of the Republic has already signed framework agreements on the implementation of eight investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the dependency of the territory from the city-building enterprise LLC "Abakansky Mine".
