The authorities of the Orenburg region did the same.
There, in the city of Novotrojsk will also be created a territory of advanced socio-economic development.
This will diversify the economy of the monogroup, reduce its dependence on the city-building enterprise of Ural Steel, as well as create more than 2,3 thousand jobs and attract investment of more than 8 billion rubles.
The list of types of economic activities in which a special legal regime for entrepreneurs will apply will include, in particular, freshwater fishing, food production, medicines and medical materials.
Novotrojsk became the first of the monogates of the Orenburg region to obtain the status of TOR.
The territory of advanced development is an economic zone with favourable tax conditions, simplified by administrative procedures and other privileges, which is created to attract investments and improve the lives of the population.
Among the benefits for residents of the TOR can be distinguished as follows: income tax not more than 5% over the first five years, and not less than 10% over the next 5 years, social contributions of 7.6% over the course of 10 years, the use of the free customs zone regime, the preferential mode of connection to various infrastructure facilities, as well as the preferential rates on the rental fee.
